<br>
Regular reclaim returns one tenth the pet's current hitpoints in mana, so 49 Earth with a Shovel returns 266 mana when reclaimed.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Improved Reclaim</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is a passive ability that permanently changes the way the reclaimed mana is calculated to be 90-99% of the nominal, stated mana cost, regardless of how injured the pet is.<br>
<br>
I do not have either the epic or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Improved Reclaim</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, so I cannot say how it works with the epic, except at one point it was broken and might still be.<br>
<br>
Best case: 200% specialization conjuration, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Spell Casting Mastery 3, Summoning Efficiency 3</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->:<br>
<br>
Normal reclaim of focused 49 Earth, costs 140 mana to cast, gains 266 mana, or 126 mana gained per reclaim.<br>
<br>
With <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Improved Reclaim</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> reclaiming any <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Greater Vocaration</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, costs 280 mana to cast, returns 380 mana, or 100 gained per reclaim.<br>
<br>
Less mana, but can use fighting pet to reclaim.  Also <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>very</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> useful for reclaiming pets after a fight.<br>
<br>
So basically you are trading a little less mana when doing straight cannibalization, for more mana when reclaiming at the end of fights.  Really depends on fighting style.<br>
